TopicTitle: The Official Kerbin Cup Tournament Thread - Final Entries Posted

Articles.Content:
If the teams who weren't chosen would like to compete in their own tournament, it *would* be kind of fun to pit the Kerbin Cup winner against the winner of, I don't know, the "Kerbal Championship League?"

I am completely guessing based off of the "first of many challenges" bit. One of many. Not just enough to eliminate down to one winner. Don't take my word, compare it to what you think. It is guess work on my end, which is why I'm asking for confirmation from someone. It would be kinda lame if everyone who volunteered (which is a pretty solid count) didn't get more than a two days notice in a complete forum vs. reddit competition. It couldn't be that hard to post a challenge every week/pick teams/set a winners vote every week (Yes its more complicated than that and thank you sooo much Rowsdower for setting this up). I'd run it if people would still play it, though if it was an individual challenge and not forum wide, much fewer people would play. That's what I'm basing my guess work off of.
